Herein, it is for the purpose of the four perversions’ eradication that the Blessed One teaches and describes the four foundations of mindfulness : when someone abides contemplating the body as a body, he eradicates his perversion that there is beauty in the ugly. So it can be stated too with respect to feelings, cognizance, and ideas.
Quiet and insight ; non-greed, non-hate, and non-delusion ; perception of impermanence, perception of pain, perception of not-self, and perception of ugliness.
Non-hate has the characteristic of non-ill-will ; its footing is abstention from killing-breathing-things.
