 came from the sky to the midst of the forest. Citra & Supaṇṇa are their names.
But the Buddha made the nāga kings safe, made them secure from Supaṇṇa.
Addressing one another with affectionate words, the nāgas & Supaṇṇas made the Buddha their refuge.
